## When I'm stuck, remember

- I've passed harder things before.  ([list one])
- Every lab I solve is one step closer.
- Going slow on one tool ISN'T thoroughness - it's avoidance of
  the hard "what's my next hypothesis?" question.
- The exam doesn't reward effort. It rewards FINDING the bug.
  If 15 minutes haven't found it, switch angle, don't dig deeper.
- I CAN ask for help. PortSwigger's solutions page exists. Using
  it for ONE step is not failure - failing the whole exam is failure.
- Stuck = I forgot which phase I'm in. Re-read the phases above.
  If I'm 30 min into phase 3 with no progress, drop the lead and
  go back to my phase 2 list.
- Stuck on host A for >30 min? Switch to host B. Fresh eyes find
  things tired eyes miss; you can come back to A later.

